My darling girl, you misunderstand. What we offer is eternal life. A chance to be part of a new...

{{GM}}Jessica suddenly notices you and her words fail in her throat.{{/GM}}

You... you're alive?

{{GM}}Her tear-streaked face freezes with a sudden realization.{{/GM}}

Oh God... The other nests... They're in every major city...

What have we done?

Am I to believe that my drunken sot of a brother hired you to find the person who killed him *after* he died?

{{GM}}Her boardroom mask drops momentarily, and in a sigh, she reveals a brief glimpse of real emotion.{{/GM}}

I left Seattle to get away from Sam and his bullshit. Now I’m back, he’s dead, and I *still* have to deal with him.

{{GM}}Jessica's demeanor instantly changes, from reluctant to helpful in the span of a single meditative breath.{{/GM}}

Maybe you can do things in a way that the police can’t. And maybe I can help.

What do you need from me?

Then, after our father died, things began to change. And we couldn't get back to a new normal. With our dad around, there was always a reassuring order to our lives. But after, everything got mixed up.

You can never really appreciate the importance of a person in your life until they’re gone.

{{GM}}The remorse plays wet across her eyes, and it seems that she's not just talking about her father.{{/GM}}

{{GM}}Jessica then steels herself to tell the rest.{{/GM}}

Sam tried to be “the man of the house”. He truly did. But he couldn't handle it, and pretty soon he had spent every dime of our father's life insurance. Every dime. After that was gone - with Mom working two, three jobs - he spent all her money, too.

I couldn’t stand the way he abused her trust... so finally, I just had to leave.

{{GM}}Her eyes widen at the edge in your voice.{{/GM}}

I'm sure Father O'Malley doesn't appreciate such a tone on these grounds.

Father, if you'll excuse us?

{{GM}}She shudders, shakes it off.{{/GM}}

Fine. Whatever. 

I want that woman dead now more than ever. If you go after her again, you think of me, okay? I’ll be around - locked and loaded.

Thanks. Mrs. Kubota will have me working it off for the rest of my life.

{{GM}}She notices your expression.{{/GM}}

You look like you’ve got something on your mind.

{{GM}}Coyote looks genuinely sad{{/GM}}

I can’t say I’m surprised he’s dead. Sam was on a downward spiral for a long time. 

What can I tell you?

{{GM}}She smiles at Paco.{{/GM}}

Easy lover.

No, it wasn’t like that. We were friends. I guess I knew him the best of everyone here. Sorry he’s gone.

{{GM}}She bites her lower lip.{{/GM}}

I like gingers.

Anyway, Jake and Sam were having a few... well, Jake was having a few. Sam was tossing ‘em back but good. Eventually, he got loud, the way he sometimes did when he mixed drinking and who-knows-what and Mrs. Kubota wanted him ejected.

{{GM}}She thinks.{{/GM}}

Enemies? That’s hard to say. Sam partied hard and when he did, he ran his mouth off pretty good. Got his ass kicked on more than one occasion. 

But no, I don’t think he had any enemies. At least none that I’m aware of.

Yeah, I did! He mentioned her once or twice. It didn't sound like they got along that well.

{{GM}}She thinks.{{/GM}}

He was rambling on about her the last time I saw him. By that point, he was completely gone. I really couldn't follow what he was saying - but he sounded miserable.

Hard to say. He’s pretty burnt. Malnourished and dehydrated too. Paco’s taking care of him. He’s got friends who know about that kind of thing. 

{{GM}}She smiles.{{/GM}}

He’s a good man, that Paco.

I’m not stopping. Not now, not ever. 

{{GM}}She looks at Paco, then back at you.{{/GM}}

A real rain is coming to Seattle - and it’s gonna wash the scum off the streets. I am going to burn every mother-fragging BTL shop in the Sprawl until they are GONE.

There is no one else available tonight. She knows that. 

The two of us will have a long talk when I see her again...

{{GM}}She stops. Sees your expression.{{/GM}}

I’m not stopping. Not now, not ever. 

{{GM}}She looks at Paco. Back at you. The Angel of Death.{{/GM}}

A real rain is coming to Seattle - and it’s gonna wash the scum off the streets. I am going to burn every mother-fragging BTL shop in the Sprawl until they are GONE.

{{GM}}Coyote grins. First time.{{/GM}}

Well, I’m gonna grab Paco, head back to the Union, maybe watch a trid or something. And I could use a long shower, too.

After that...

{{GM}}Her jaw sets, her eyes harden, and she’s Coyote again.{{/GM}}

Let them come. If the Yakuza wants me, they’re gonna find me. Nothing I can do about that. 

Some people choose to live in fear but not me. Not today.

No one’s innocent. 

{{GM}}She looks at you both.{{/GM}}

Not us, not anyone in the Sprawl. But they’re chip-heads not pushers. They have a problem. They didn’t ask for this.

No one’s innocent. 

{{GM}}She looks at you both.{{/GM}}

Not us, not anyone in the Sprawl. But they’re chip-heads not pushers. They have a problem. They didn’t ask for this.

{{GM}}Suddenly, the Baron’s flowery speech is gone, and he’s all business.{{/GM}}

Get to a secure jackpoint. Enter Shadowlands. I will meet you there. Bon voyage!

{{GM}}The Baron grins and his image flickers away.{{/GM}}

{{GM}}The faux French accent is gone, replaced by cold fear.{{/GM}}

I've got three Telestrian deckers closing on me! They've... How the hell? I'm gonna have to eject. Oh, man - dumpshock's a bitch!

You have to get out of there! Get out RIGHT NOW!

{{GM}}All his pretense drops.{{/GM}}

I've run solid interference for you but I can't hold these guys off much longer. I'm good but... but I'm not *that* good. 

My plan will work. You've got to trust me.

{{GM}}The voice modulation returns. So does the French accent.{{/GM}}

One day, they will make trivids about our adventure together! But that is for another time.

Now, here is what you must do...

{{GM}}The voice modulation returns. So does the French accent.{{/GM}}

One day, they will make trivids about our adventure together! But that is for another time.

Now, here is what you must do...

My but aren’t you a big, powerful $(l.Race). Are you enjoying the Seamstresses Union? There should be plenty for a $(l.man) like you to enjoy. 

{{GM}}She eyes you closely.{{/GM}}

Or is this business?

My, but aren’t you the pretty elf! Are you enjoying the Seamstresses Union? There should be plenty for a $(l.man) like you to enjoy.

{{GM}}She eyes you closely.{{/GM}}

Or is this business?

It is true what they say: "Good things come in small packages!" Are you enjoying the Seamstresses Union? There should be plenty for a $(l.man) like you to enjoy.

{{GM}}She eyes you closely.{{/GM}}

Or is this business?

Konbanwa! Good evening! Are you enjoying the Seamstresses Union? There should be plenty for a $(l.man) like you to enjoy.

{{GM}}She eyes you closely.{{/GM}}

Or is this business?

But not tempted enough? 

{{GM}}She laughs.{{/GM}}

Tell me, omae - what is it you're looking for?

Ohayo! Would you like some...

{{GM}}She stops.{{/GM}}

Forgive me, omae, but you look like hell.

Fascinating again!

Detective McKlusky isn't interested in anything but Detective McKlusky. He'd convict his own mother if it meant another 10 nuyen a week in his paycheck. Plus, he's on the take. {{GM}}Dresden pauses, considering.{{/GM}}

You have honor, after a fashion. I try to honor the dead in my work, so we have that in common.

Well, no one can say he didn’t have it coming, am I right? 

{{GM}}He frowns at himself.{{/GM}}

That was a double-negative.

{{GM}}He holds your gaze.{{/GM}}

It means someone very powerful in the Matrix has an interest in you all of a sudden, and that doesn’t happen by accident. 

Calls himself Baron Samedi. He’s been asking about you on Shadowlands. He has a pretty distinctive icon - skull face with a top hat.

{{GM}}He shakes his head.{{/GM}}

I’m not sure I want to know. But that’s not what I’m talking about.

Someone’s been asking about you on Shadowlands. Calls himself Baron Samedi. He has a pretty distinctive icon - skull face with a top hat.

Hmm... sounds like you two have already met, then. 

{{GM}}He frowns.{{/GM}}

Well this Baron, he’s been asking about you on Shadowlands. Strange guy. Has a pretty distinctive icon - skull face with a tophat.

Hans dear, I love you but you could babble on forever and I believe time is of the essence. 

{{GM}}The painted elf addresses you.{{/GM}}

$(l.name), is it? Delighted. The bug you fought was not merely a magically-Awakened animal like a wyvern or hydra or anything else in the Sixth World. In fact, it isn’t from *this* world at all. It’s the physical embodiment of an insect spirit from another plane of existence.

It is indeed! I am pleased that you are not gullible enough to fall for that line of metaphysical bullshit. 

{{GM}}He bows with a flourish.{{/GM}}

I am Har'lea'quinn. The Lightbearer. Last Knight of the Crying Spire. He who manipulates shadowrunners and fights duels with assholes. And for the next hour or two, I am at your service.

Goo goo g'joob! 

{{GM}}He bows with a flourish.{{/GM}}

I am Har'lea'quinn. The Lightbearer. Last Knight of the Crying Spire. He who manipulates shadowrunners and fights duels with assholes. And for the next hour or two, I am at your service.

{{GM}}He points at someone in the crowd and smiles. The man sees him pointing and smiles back.{{/GM}}

That guy there? He’s with Ares Macrotechnology. Enormous megacorp. Ridiculously powerful. They’ve been sniffing around Project Aegis for quite awhile now. Clearly, they have an agenda that’s just starting to unfold.

{{GM}}He gives the Ares man the finger. The man smiles and returns the gesture.{{/GM}}

{{GM}}Harlequin rolls his eyes.{{/GM}}

Nooooo. Of course they’re not. Government agencies are well known for their perspicacity. And there’s no racism in government. That was wiped out in the 20th Century!

This is getting fun.

{{GM}}He laughs.{{/GM}}

Just the opposite, schmuck. The lesson is this - the game is rigged. The cards are stacked. The dice are loaded. 

It’s the same as it always was. Every cycle. People in power exert power. Little people cower in their homes, think what they’re told to think, and buy whatever product will help them forget how horrible their lives are for another day.

{{GM}}Harlequin winks.{{/GM}}

Not working for ya?

{{GM}}Then, he lets out a big sigh.{{/GM}}

Okay, look.

Death and I have an understanding. He doesn’t bother me and I don’t bother him. 

{{GM}}He rolls his eyes.{{/GM}}

Okay, that’s not really true. The truth is that there are some things you can’t know, kid. Insects from another dimension only scratch the surface of what’s really going on in the Sixth World. And the idea that anyone knows what’s really going on is kinda nuts in itself.

{{GM}}Harlequin winks.{{/GM}}

I’m kinda fuzzy on that concept. 

{{GM}}Then, he lets out a big sigh.{{/GM}}

Okay, look.

It would not be the first written about me, to be sure!

I shall consider it! Now, onward!

{{GM}}You hear him muttering rhymes to himself as he walks.{{/GM}}

{{GM}}She laughs.{{/GM}} 

No. 

She *shot* a coyote once, thinking it was a shaman who double-crossed her. We’ve been calling her Coyote ever since.

{{GM}}She laughs.{{/GM}} 

No. 

She *shot* a coyote once, thinking it was a shaman who double-crossed her. We’ve been calling her Coyote ever since.

{{GM}}She nods.{{/GM}} 

Sam was a regular customer and a regular pain in the ass for as long as I’ve been here. Talked a big game but he was always broke. As soon as he got any money in his pocket, it went straight to his head - chips, drugs, or booze. 

Coyote had a soft spot for him, though.

My God. Shane. 

{{GM}}She looks at her customers, then down at the bar top for a long moment before finally composing herself.{{/GM}}

Thanks for letting me know. Maybe we’ll talk later.

So, where's Jessica now? 

{{GM}}She whispers.{{/GM}}

Is she... with the guy from the asylum?

{{GM}}He sighs.{{/GM}}

Really $(l.sir), you are becoming tedious. I have matters to attend to. You may benefit from them or I will have McKlusky will feed you to something and bury the excretion. 

What do you believe Project Aegis does?

I find your bluntness somehow refreshing. 

{{GM}}He touches a button on the desk.{{/GM}}

Mr. Quoth, please ask my daughter to join us.

{{GM}}The already cold exterior of James Telestrian III turns to ice.{{/GM}}

I see. It was you and your crippled little friend who leaked Aegis to this $(l.man). We will speak of it later - in private.

Now then, $(l.name), there are people I wish you to meet - the "committee" my daughter alluded to. This is a rare opportunity for a $(l.man) of the streets such as yourself. I urge you to behave. We will adjourn to the library.

{{GM}}He pauses before answering.{{/GM}} 

The host for the Queen is chosen very carefully as the interactions between the Queen and lead shaman are critical - a family connection between the two roles is ideal. As you have discovered my father’s... indiscretion with Melinda Watts, you know that Jessica Watts - the shaman, and Marie-Louise are related by blood.

I would appreciate if that information remained in the shadows.

{{GM}}His eyes say, “I’d love to kill you now” but his mouth continues its smirk.{{/GM}} 

I got one of the richest an' most powerful men in the the Pacific Northwest takin’ care of me, dumbass. 

Wadda YOU got?

{{GM}}His smirk gets even bigger.{{/GM}} 

Nooo. You go ahead in there and keep talkin’ trash. That should work out fine for you, drek-for-brains! 

You got no money and you got no power. So, what DO you got?

{{GM}}His eyes widen. Then his smirk gets even broader.{{/GM}} 

That's the right attitude, chummer! You're just the same as Mr. Telestrian. Yes you are!

The only difference is that you got no money and you got no power. So, tell me again, drek-for-brains. What is it you got?

{{GM}}He scratches his mop of red hair.{{/GM}}

I guess that concludes the story of “$(l.name) and the Dead Man’s Switch”, huh? 

Y’know, I’ve been thinking, maybe you should stay in Seattle awhile. There’s plenty of ways folks like us can get into trouble here - you only skimmed the surface.

Hmmmm.

{{GM}}Jake grabs the dead man by the throat. At first it looks like he’s trying to kill him again, and then you notice he’s feeling for something under the skin.{{/GM}}

Yep, he’s got a corp ID chip.

{{GM}}As you approach the scene of Sam's murder, Jake spies the flashing red and blue lights up ahead.{{/GM}}

Whoa, hold up a minute. Lone Star isn't above collecting on a corp issued bounty, and the one on my head isn't going away any time soon. 

{{GM}}He sighs.{{/GM}}

Whatever you say, kid.

{{GM}}With one swift move, she sinks a syringe into Coyote’s thigh.{{/GM}}

Nighty-night.

{{GM}}His eyes widen at the question.{{/GM}}

You mistake your importance, $(l.name). No, I was not spying on you. Until Mr. Telestrian’s summons, you were beneath my notice. I saw only a customer.

Now, do you require my magic?

{{GM}}Aljernon's face takes on a dreamy expression.{{/GM}}

Are any of us? 

Yes, $(l.name), I am here. And at the Seamstresses Union. And a myriad of other places. On to the work at hand. Do you require my magic?

And what, I'm supposed to take your word for it?

{{GM}}He makes eye contact. Hesitates.{{/GM}}

Fine, I'll speculate. But only because I can find you if this doesn't pan out. 2,500. No more.

{{GM}}$(s.name) is busy talking on his commlink, checking his heads-up display, and motioning to a runner standing nearby - all at the same time. He's an intense little man. You get the sense that he likes to look busy.{{/GM}}

I'm $(s.name). Make it quick. Biz is good. 

Talk to me.

Oh, hey $(l.guy). One more thing.

{{GM}}He covers his commlink for a moment. Tilts his head your way but you can see he’s still staring at his HUD.{{/GM}}

I'm a fence too. If you got anything you need to unload, come see me.

Hey $(l.guy)! Wait a minute.

{{GM}}He covers his commlink for a moment. Tilts his head your way but you can see he’s still staring at his HUD.{{/GM}}

I'm a fence. If you got anything you need to unload, you come see me.

{{GM}}$(s.name) is busy talking on his commlink, checking his heads-up display, and motioning to a runner standing nearby - all at the same time. He's an intense little man. You get the sense that he likes to look busy.{{/GM}}

I'm $(s.name). Make it quick. Biz is good. 

Talk to me.

When they enter that room back there, they will have no thoughts other than thoughts of promotion. With the Ripper in hand, my brother will be forgotten, along with all the other victims. But so too will I.

They will not be a problem.

{{GM}}Whether that's true or not, Shannon's confidence and very presence seem capable of making it true.{{/GM}}

That's the one. 

{{GM}}He pockets it.{{/GM}}

Okay, you done good. But you're late. And Coyote knows that in this case, late equals no payment. But, I’m feeling magnanimous tonight so you guys can can keep the rest of the gems as your reward.

{{GM}}Mr. Delilah looks you up and down. Takes you all in.{{/GM}}

Listen, you look like the sort of $(l.man) who might run a crew of your own one day. Might need a little talent. When that happens, you come to me. I'll set you up.

{{GM}}He dismisses you with a wave.{{/GM}}

