{{GM}}When he speaks, the ork’s voice is soft and thoughtful, and he talks almost exclusively in numbers: calibers, ranges, rounds per second, arc of fire, razoring factor, tensile strength and, of course, price.{{/GM}}

Bunker Buster Gruberman, at your service. Friends call me Buster. I also answer to Sergeant, Sir, and even Theodore on occasion. Anytime you're in the market for firearms, ammunition, or ordinance, I’m your man.

How can I help you?

{{GM}}Sam’s smiles a toothy smile. {{/GM}} 

I've been waiting for this all night. New Larry has something he wants to say, don'tcha Larry? 

Go ahead, spill it.

{{GM}}Something dawns on him. He leans in to New Larry - amused and dangerous.{{/GM}}

We were set up... and he knows it... don’tcha Larry? What was that call you made before we hit Renraku? 

How come you couldn't geek that guy before he unloaded on Dowd? I've seen you fling a lightning bolt, son. He shoulda been burnt toast before his gun cleared the holster.

Contact my law firm - Rogers, Mengert & McCain - when the job is done. They'll know what to do. 

{{GM}}He turns to his left.{{/GM}}

Chet?

{{GM}}The screen leaps to life, making you squint against its brightness. The face on the screen is laughing – Sam Watts.{{/GM}}

Hey, buddy. Hope I didn't catch you at a bad time. 

{{GM}}He giggles. He’s drunk again. Or worse.{{/GM}}

NULL SWEAT. Don’t go ballistic on me! Metaphorically or otherwise!

{{GM}}He points to himself.{{/GM}}

Sam. Sam Watts. I’m just picking up a little shipment that fell off a truck. Looks like those ass-wipe longshoreman left the crates spread out across the whole damn dock. Serves me right for not tipping them, I guess. Now come on - who are you guys?

{{GM}}The young elf woman is clearly shaken from being locked up and seeing her jailer killed in front of her eyes.{{/GM}}

Th-these people are insane! I’ve been a prisoner all night. And I heard noises...

{{GM}}She shudders.{{/GM}}

{{GM}}She looks pained. Sighs.{{/GM}}

I suppose. We have money. A lot of money.

Listen, we’ve got to get out of here! The priests and acolytes have been going down that hole since they locked me up. They were chanting all the way but then I heard screaming. And something else. Something... foul.

{{GM}}She sighs. Coming down off the adrenaline rush.{{/GM}}

Marie... Marie-Louise. 

Listen, we’ve got to get out of here! The priests and acolytes have been going down that hole since they locked me up. They were chanting all the way but then I heard screaming. And something else. Something... foul.

{{GM}}She's glassy-eyed. Maybe in shock.{{/GM}}

That was... I don't know. That was bad. Really bad.

I'm out of here. Sorry...

{{GM}}He flashes his pearly-whites again.{{/GM}}

Exactly. But it has to be now. Renraku's shipping Saada out of Seattle in the morning for some sort of overseas research project. Tonight, he's being kept at a hidden research facility out here in the Barrens. Just a couple miles from here. I hear they’ve been bringing in unmarked shipments for weeks now, thinking that nobody notices.

We don’t care about any of that. We just want Saada - before he's out of our reach.

{{GM}}He flashes his pearly-whites again.{{/GM}}

Exactly. But it has to be now. Renraku's shipping Saada out of Seattle in the morning for some sort of overseas research project. Tonight, he's being kept at a hidden research facility out here in the Barrens. Just a couple miles from here. I hear they’ve been bringing in unmarked shipments for weeks now, thinking that nobody notices.

We don’t care about any of that. We just want Saada - before he's out of our reach.

The place should be lightly guarded - probably rent-a-cops. Get in, grab Saada, and get out. In exchange, I'm authorized to remit 9,000 nuyen in payment.

{{GM}}He fixes you with a hard stare.{{/GM}}

I am not, however, authorized to negotiate.

{{GM}}He smiles with his mouth but his eyes say "predator".{{/GM}}

Who knows? Could be anything. Probably someone riding the wrong end of a Yakuza execution BTL. We get all kinds.

I can hook you up, if you're interested.

Yes, for what *that's* worth. He's the reason I was at the Universal Brotherhood in first place. I was running away from *him*.

Now... Now, I can’t sleep at all... I’m afraid that *this* is a dream and that I’ll wake up and and still be there... with the... bugs.

{{GM}}She shudders.{{/GM}}

Father didn’t approve of my boyfriend and tried to scare him off. Something went wrong and Harkeem ended up in a wheelchair. Father covered the whole thing up and lied to me about Harkeem. He told me horrible things. 

{{GM}}Her jaw clenches.{{/GM}} 

And I believed him.

Aunt Lynne was very excited to have me there. Almost manic. She talked about the Inner Circle and how I was going to be at its center. She said I would be their queen. The way she spoke - it was as if she’d seen God or something. 

{{GM}}Her eyes close and she hugs herself tightly.{{/GM}} 

But it’s not God she sees. It’s bugs. Only bugs.

{{GM}}She smiles. In love.{{/GM}} 

Yes, even after my father ruined his life and convinced me to hate him, he’s still been watching over me. My angel in cyberspace - Baron Samedi.

After we escaped, I told Harkeem about the Brotherhood and about the bugs. It was his idea to steal Project Aegis so you could go back into the Universal Brotherhood and exterminate the bugs. But I don’t know how he knew about it. Baron Samedi just... knows things.

{{GM}}She smiles.{{/GM}}

It's Seattle.

You look like you have a question.

Hmm. Doc Castle's equipment isn't really set up for that.

{{GM}}He considers for a minute.{{/GM}}

However... I could employ a semiconductor chip... it could decode DNA using a voltage change, instead of light. That would eliminate the use of highly expensive equipment that would be required otherwise.

No drek? 

{{GM}}He turns to Johnny, excited.{{/GM}}

Wake up, Johnny-boy. You've got work to do. And $(l.name), if you need any gear, I'll be right here.

{{GM}}You hear the clicking of a keyboard.{{/GM}}

Might of happened when they upgraded you to being a Mother ... I mean Father. 

Welcome to the Inner Sanctum.

{{GM}}He fixes you with a stare.{{/GM}}

I'm very scared. 

Now let's try that again. Who the hell are you?

You're right. There is no reason I should let Security push me around.

{{GM}}He steels himself.{{/GM}}

Just do it quick!

Hey... thanks! {{GM}}The officer's face lights up as he takes a sip. He seems pretty trusting, for an officer of the law.{{/GM}}

You know... when my dad was a cop... this was back when cops actually worked for the government... he said folks would buy him coffee all the time. But I ain't seen it 'till now. 

So what can I do for you?

{{GM}}A filthy guard is looking into an open vent. He is clearly not enjoying the idea of climbing back into the duct.{{/GM}}

Sorry I tracked that drek all over the floor. 

{{GM}}He shakes his head.{{/GM}}

Man, I can't believe what happened to the night watch.

{{GM}}He lets out a sigh.{{/GM}}

Duty ABOVE All. It's Mr. Silverstar's favorite.

I can't believe anyone can spout Telestrian Corporate Values when a bunch of our guys were geeked a few hours ago.

{{GM}}As the Telestrian tech jockey turns to speak, you a notice a panel has been removed from one of the LAN racks just behind him.{{/GM}}

Thanks for coming. Can you believe it? Silverstar is calling it an "intrusion" but I know the aftermath of a shadowrun when I see it. 

Start over in the corner and make sure you don't get any solvents on my servers.

{{GM}}He crosses his arms.{{/GM}}

Do you swallow every line our corp overlords spout at you? You look smarter than that.

Whatever. Just get this place cleaned up and get out.

{{GM}}She pulls her hair back to show you. No implant.

Then her mouth tightens and her eyes well up in tears.{{/GM}}

I do. I know. Lost my husband. Lost my son. My daughter... they use her...

{{GM}}The camera swivels to show a well-dressed man sitting next to Sam.{{/GM}} 

Persuant to Mr. Watts' wishes, Rogers, Mengert & McCain has installed a secure dedicated phone line so you may contact us directly when the task is complete. We will then begin a verification process. Note that you must also be on a secure land-line to access this number. We will not accept transmissions from commlinks or other devices. 

{{GM}}The camera swivels back to Sam.{{/GM}}

{{GM}}Sam still looks like drek. Same clothes, same background. Probably shot at the same time as the first video.{{/GM}}

